    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 1:31-34",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Deuteronomy 1:31-34",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Bare thee — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Or ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "carried thee, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "as a father carries his weak and tender child in his arms, through difficulties and dangers, gently leading you according as you were able to go, and sustaining you by his power and goodness. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Ye did not believe the Lord — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "So they ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "could not enter in, because of unbelief. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "It was not any other sin that shut them out of Canaan, but their disbelief of that promise which was typical of gospel grace; to signify that no sin will ruin us but ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "unbelief, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "which is a sin against the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "remedy, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and therefore without remedy. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Your words — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "That is to say, your murmurings, your unthankful, impatient, distrustful, and rebellious speeches.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
